```rust
fn route_next_hop(f: &Frontier, rel: &Relation, cm: &CompositeMemory,
                  cb: &AtomMemory) -> Frontier {
    if f.atoms.len() < 40 {
        // EXACT path: each atom is discrete. XOR-unbind directly. No SNR loss.
        let mut out = Vec::new();
        for (atom, score) in &f.atoms {
            // exact composite lookup: a XOR rel.mask -> stored target bits
            let target_bits = cm.lookup_xor(atom, &rel.mask);     // BinaryAtom
            out.push((target_bits, *score));
        }
        Frontier { bundle: FrontierBundle::rebuild_from_atoms(&out, M), atoms: out }
    } else {
        // STATISTICAL path: too many to track exactly, use count bundle.
        f.hop(rel, cb)
    }
}
```

**This is the dual algebra made concrete:** the frontier *self-selects* its algebra by size. Small frontier → XOR (exact, cheap, no loss). Large frontier → count (statistical, SNR-gated, but N-independent cost). The crossover at ~40 is set by CompositeMemory's interference limit from Debate C.

